gr.interamerican.bo2.impl.open.runtime
Class ProviderImpl

java.lang.Object
  gr.interamerican.bo2.impl.open.runtime.ProviderImpl
All Implemented Interfaces:
Provider
public class ProviderImpl
extends Object
implements Provider

Base implementation of Provider. This class realizes a basic implementation of Provider. Different subclasses of Provider are stored in a Map with the Provider subclass as key. The getProvider(subclass) method will try to get a Provider of the specified subclass from the Map. If no such provider is found, then the object will try to create a Provider of this type.

close

public void close()
           throws DataException
Description copied from interface: Provider
Closes all resources of this provider. This method will not call any transaction manager functionality. Transaction management is done explicitly via the transaction manager. This method does only cleanup of the resources.
